.TH AMALGAMATE 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
amalgamate \- merge nearby polygons in a triangulated PSLG
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B amalgamate
.I lengthlimit
.I arealimit
.I input
.I output
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B amalgamate
combines neighbouring polygons in a constrained Delaunay triangulation
into larger polygons. It is used to make dense archipelagos and
similar areas render acceptably on small\(hyscale maps: removing all
small islands would leave the area too empty, while drawing every
outline at the given resolution would make it look uniformly dark.
.PP
The program reads three files generated by the earlier pipeline
steps:
.IR input .node ,
.IR input .poly
(produced by
.BR shape2triangle (1))
and
.IR input .ele
(produced by Shewchuk's
.B triangle
.RB ( "triangle \-pcAI input" )).
A triangle is accepted into the amalgamated output when either it
already lies inside one of the original polygons or all three of its
edges are shorter than
.IR lengthlimit
kilometres. The accepted triangles are merged into polygons; polygons
smaller than
.I arealimit
square kilometres are then dropped.
.PP
The resulting
.IR output .node
and
.IR output .poly
files describe the new polygon set; an
.I output.ele
file is not produced and may be regenerated with
.RB \(lq "triangle \-cpI output" \(rq
if needed.
.PP
A typical full pipeline is:
.PP
.RS 4
shape2triangle 5 input/ponet suomi
.br
triangle \-pcAI suomi
.br
amalgamate 4 100 suomi suomi.1
.br
triangle2shape 0 suomi.1 suomishape
.RE
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I lengthlimit
Maximum allowed triangle\(hyedge length, in kilometres. Triangles with
an edge longer than this are not used to bridge polygons.
.TP
.I arealimit
Minimum polygon area in square kilometres; smaller polygons are
dropped from the output. Pass
.B 0
to disable the filter.
.TP
.I input
Stem of the input PSLG files
.RI ( input .node ", " input .poly ", " input .ele ).
.TP
.I output
Stem of the output PSLG files. The special value
.B \-debug
overwrites
.I input.ele
with the triangles selected for amalgamation, leaving the
.I .node
and
.I .poly
files unchanged.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shape2triangle (1),
.BR triangle2shape (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-shapetools/issues>.
